-- Hitachi, Lithuania to Sign Preliminary Nuclear Deal Tomorrow
-- B y   M i l d a   S e p u t y t e
-- 2011-12-22T13:41:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-22/hitachi-lithuania-to-sign-preliminary-nuclear-deal-tomorrow.html
The Lithuanian government and
 Hitachi Ltd. (6501)  will sign a preliminary agreement tomorrow to build
and finance a nuclear power plant in the country.  The concession agreement will be signed in Vilnius, the
Energy Ministry said in an e-mailed statement.  Hitachi will sign the final contract to begin building the
400 billion-yen ($5.1 billion) project next year, company
President Hiroaki Nakanishi said on Dec. 20. The plant, to be
built by Hitachi-GE Nuclear Energy Ltd., a venture with General
Electric Co., is scheduled to be operational in 2020, said
Hitachi,  Japan â€™s second-largest builder of nuclear reactors.  To contact the reporter on this story:
